      "description": "Dartagnan is a bounded model checker for concurrent C/C++ programs under various weak memory models (TSO, ARM, POWER, RISC-V, Linux kernel, C11/RC11).  It operates on full LLVM bitcode programs via Boogie/Z3 and can verify reachability and state assertions.  It includes a portability analysis mode (Porthos) that checks whether a program that is safe under one memory model is also safe under a weaker model.",
